Ultra-realistic cinematic collage of three photographs, vertical 9:16, no AI flatness, no invented elements, everything strictly defined for a stable and repeatable result. Preserve the exact facial features, proportions, and expression from the reference photo across all frames. Shot on a professional Canon Mark J7 with direct on-camera flash, strong Y2K flash aesthetic: crisp highlights, deep contrast, hard yet realistic shadows, visible texture, subtle grain, evening interior exposure.

Frame 1 (wide establishing shot):
Evening interior of a classic European mansion staircase made of dark polished wood with elegant carved railings and deep shadows. Warm wooden floor continues into the base of the staircase. In the extreme foreground, dominating most of the lower frame, a very low but extremely wide white basket overflowing with more than 2000 dense red roses, tightly packed heads, realistic scale and depth. Behind the basket at the base of the staircase, the woman sits barefoot on the floor, body turned slightly away. Massive glossy red foil heart balloons rise upward along the staircase, long curling red ribbons cascading naturally and filling the vertical space. She turns her head over her shoulder, looking directly into the camera.

Frame 2 (medium shot, diagonal angle):
Camera slightly lower and closer, angled diagonally for a candid paparazzi feel. The basket still fills the lower half of the frame. The dark wooden staircase with carved details is clearly visible behind her. She adjusts the balloon ribbons with one hand, posture elegant and relaxed. Fitted black long-sleeve dress with deep open back, fabric naturally hugging the silhouette. Hair styled in a high updo with soft loose curls, slightly messy, natural face-framing strands. Direct flash sharply defines the texture of roses, glossy balloon reflections, wood grain of the staircase, and natural skin texture.

Frame 3 (close-up portrait):
Tight crop on her face and shoulders. She holds a single red rose delicately near her face, stem angled upward. Her gaze turned to the side, not into the camera. Expression soft and thoughtful. Loose strands catch the flash. Background fades into darker wooden staircase shadows with subtle hints of red balloon reflections. Strong depth, dramatic Valentine‚Äôs Day mood, candid luxury, alive, real, and unstaged.
